Subject: kmsgrab: fall back to crtc geometry when card isn't in card_descriptors

Apollo builds its `card_descriptors` list once, inside `kms_display_names()`,
called during startup probing. The list maps each `/dev/dri/cardN` path to
its monitors (CRTC → viewport). It's a static `std::vector<card_descriptor_t>`
and never refreshed.

When a virtual EVDI display is created mid-session (by the patched
VDISPLAY::createVirtualDisplay flow), the new `/dev/dri/card0` does not
exist in `card_descriptors`. So when KMS screencast init scans `/dev/dri`,
finds a plane with `fb_id` on the new EVDI card, and tries to look the
card up:

    auto pos = std::find_if(begin(card_descriptors), end(card_descriptors),
                            [&](card_descriptor_t &cd) { return cd.path == filestring; });
    if (pos == end(card_descriptors)) {
      BOOST_LOG(error) << "Couldn't find [" << entry.path()
                       << "]: This shouldn't have happened :/";
      return -1;
    }

…it bails with `-1`, every encoder probe fails, and the Steam Deck client
gets a `503 Failed to initialize video/capture encoding`.

The actual fatal log from a real session:

    Found monitor for DRM screencasting
    Error: Couldn't find ["/dev/dri/card0"]: This shouldn't have happened :/
    [repeats for nvenc → vaapi → software]
    Fatal: Unable to find display or encoder during startup.

But card_descriptors is only used to look up a viewport for the matched
crtc — and the code already has a "crtc not in crtc_to_monitor" fallback
that uses `crtc->width/height/x/y` directly. Just route the "card not in
descriptors" case to that same fallback. For an EVDI card, the crtc
geometry equals the EDID we just programmed (1280x800 for Steam Deck),
which is exactly what we want to capture.

End-to-end after this patch:

    Found monitor for DRM screencasting
    Card [/dev/dri/card0] not in card_descriptors (hotplugged after startup, e.g. EVDI); using crtc geometry
    Found connector ID [40]
    Creating encoder [hevc_vaapi]
    Color coding: SDR (Rec. 601)
    ...

--- a/src/platform/linux/kmsgrab.cpp
+++ b/src/platform/linux/kmsgrab.cpp
@@ -675,11 +675,17 @@
               return cd.path == filestring;
             });
 
-            if (pos == std::end(card_descriptors)) {
-              // This code path shouldn't happen, but it's there just in case.
-              // card_descriptors is part of the guesswork after all.
-              BOOST_LOG(error) << "Couldn't find ["sv << entry.path() << "]: This shouldn't have happened :/"sv;
-              return -1;
+            // NOTE: card_descriptors is built ONCE by kms_display_names() at
+            // startup. If the user creates a virtual EVDI display after that,
+            // its card path won't be in the list. The original code returned
+            // -1 here (the "Couldn't find ... shouldn't have happened" error),
+            // which made every encoder fail for fresh EVDI cards. We instead
+            // fall through to the same crtc-based fallback used when the
+            // viewport map lookup misses below.
+            const bool have_descriptor = (pos != std::end(card_descriptors));
+            if (!have_descriptor) {
+              BOOST_LOG(info) << "Card ["sv << entry.path()
+                              << "] not in card_descriptors (hotplugged after startup, e.g. EVDI); using crtc geometry"sv;
             }
 
